social_posts.post_text:
The big terrain park is still closed, but I found some fun jumps next to the trees. @eldoramtnresort is actually pretty dope. I’ll definitely be back!
#skieldora

LARGE BOYEEE! Huge thanks to joe for the sick follow shot! 

🎥 @coleman_cooler_joe 

#euc #electricunicycle #eucjump #eucjumps #kingsong #gotway #begode #gotwayrs #pevs #ewheels #revrides #rubyhillbikepark

Probably the toughest fall I took while trying to get the large line. I’ve gotten better about front sliding instead of rolling ever since I separated my ac joint. The only problem with the front slide though is my knee pads always seem to slip up and I still end up bruising my knees a little. I’m wearing the @officialleatt dual axis knee pads, which are good for everything except that scenario. Anyone had any luck with other knee pads that don’t slip up in front slides?

#euc #electricunicycle #eucjump #eucjumps #gotway #begode #gotwayrs #pevs #ewheels #revrides #eucfails #eucfail #euccrash

Thanks to @eridelife for letting me try the Sherman S. Didn’t get it on film, but within an hour of acclimating to the wheel, I was able to send the whole large line. I dont intend to shell out $4000 for one any time soon, but I was Impressed with this machine. Seth recorded some of my initial thoughts on the wheel, so keep an eye out for that.
#euc #electricunicycle #eucjump #eucjumps #kingsong #gotway #begode #leaperkim #shermans #veteransherman #pevs #ewheels #revrides #rubyhillbikepark
Happy 1st birthday, kiddo! Probably not a bad thing that you prefer carrots over cake. Love you so much. Thanks to everyone who showed up and celebrated with us ❤️

First time hitting rails today. Pretty stoked on my progress… apparently I don’t know how to 360 anymore though haha. Been loving @eldoramtnresort and @woodward__eldora 

#skicolorado #insta360 #eldora #terrainpark
Got a little too big for my britches at @eldoramtnresort … broke my binding off and my ski went all the way to the bottom 😂🤘
Rail Redemption at @eldoramtnresort
Lots of crashes today trying some bigger rails at @eldoramtnresort but I did hit this new one clean.

First backflip on skis at @snobahn ! Always wanted to try this. Thanks to the awesome staff for some excellent pointers and for filming 😎🤘

#skicolorado #skiflips #terrainpark #skitricks #snobahn

Me: “Hey ski, wanna try a frontflip?
My ski: “Nah I’m gonna go jump on the trampoline with the other kids” 

@snobahn 

#skicolorado #skiflips #terrainpark #skitricks #snobahn
Finally tried backflip to snow and got to see @willjamesonline for the first time in ages! Cheers to @rubyhillrailyard for the dope setup!

Landed it! @rubyhillrailyard 
🎥 @willjamesonline
2022 showreel - it wouldn’t let me go longer than 90 seconds, but I can’t be bothered to do anything about it, so here ya go…
Glad I got some laps in with @shibby_time while he was here before the snow came. Thanks for the follow shot @freshlycharged !
Large line starting to feel somewhat chill on the s22 pro. Had to fight a head wind on jump 7 though, hence the beeps. Stoked to see what goes down this season!

Hit the moon booter at Ruby Hill. This was the last jump at the park that I hadn’t hit. I’ve been obsessing about it in my head all winter… I guess I’ll have to start throwing some tricks on my s18 or something.

Thanks @denverbikeparks crew and the volunteers for making Ruby such an amazing place. Helps me get out of my head.

location.city_name: Valiant Living Professionals Program For Men

social_posts.post_text:
Sometimes desperation is the very thing we need to make the tough call to get help. In this clip from the Valiant Living Podcast, Dylan shares his story of the moment he finally had enough and decided to make some changes. Dylan and Lily’s story is incredible. You can hear the whole thing at the link in our bio or by searching “Valiant Living Podcast”. 

There’s hope for you and your loved ones too. Go to www.valiantliving.com. We’re here to help.

social_posts.post_text:
Sometimes there’s a traumatic event in our lives that sends us deeper down the road of addiction. Often times it’s because we feel like we need a way to escape and/or medicate our pain. 

A lot of the work we do is giving people the tools to know how to deal with the hardship of life. 

We’re so grateful for Dylan and Lily sharing their story. Listen to the full episode by clicking the link in our bio or by searching “Valiant Living” wherever you listen to podcasts.
